# __NAME__ — Game Spec (draft, scaffolded)

> Generated by `pnpm new-game __ID__`. Fill this in from `games/__ID__/BRIEF.md`
> (resolve its "Open for SPEC" list) **before** implementing. Follow the Bubble
> Buddies SPEC conventions: integer constants, ASCII maps where applicable, and
> explicit §determinism / §multiplayer sections. Stop for Kevin's approval of
> the spec before building the sim (ADR-009 Stage 2 protocol).

## 1. Coordinate system & units

Positions and velocities are integer **subpixels** (`SUBPX = 256` per pixel).
Tiles are `TILE_SIZE` px. Fixed 60 Hz tick. All randomness from the sim's
seeded `Rng`. _(Inherited from RetroKit — do not change.)_

## 2. Tiles & maps

Describe the tile set (solid / platform / slope as needed) and the level
dimensions. Note camera use: follow target, level size (screens), and any
forward-lock / boss-pin per the BRIEF.

## 3. Entities

One subsection per entity (player/hero, enemies, projectiles, …): hitbox,
movement constants, states. Keep every constant in `src/sim/constants.ts`.

## 4. Input

Which of the NES buttons (`Left Right Up Down A B Start`) do what.

## 5. Scoring / win & lose conditions

Round structure, scoring, and how a game ends.

## 6. Multiplayer (netcode)

Mode (co-op / versus / race — see the BRIEF). Server-authoritative per ADR-003.
Player count, CPU-fill rule if any, disconnect behavior, and which entities are
server-owned vs. client-predicted. The room hosts this game via its registry
entry in `workers/rooms/src/games.ts`.

## 7. Determinism & update order

The exact per-tick update order (sim is the source of truth for replays and
netcode). Serialized state must hash stably. The golden replay fixture lives at
`test/fixtures/replay-001.json` — regenerate intentionally with
`REGEN_FIXTURES=1 pnpm test` and review the diff alongside any spec change.

## 8. Levels / tracks / rinks

ASCII maps or data tables, as applicable.
